        "title": "Trade Sales Account Manager",
        "text": "<p><strong>Molly Mahon | Forest Row, East Sussex or London (Hybrid / Remote)</strong></p><p>Molly Mahon is entering an exciting new chapter. As we celebrate ten years of colour, craft and block print, we are looking for an exceptional <strong>Trade Sales Account Manager</strong> to help shape the next phase of our growth within the UK interiors trade market.</p><p>This is not a maintenance role. It is a build, drive and lead role.</p><p>We are looking for someone ambitious, connected and commercially sharp, someone who truly understands the fabric and wallpaper trade and believes they can go out and win meaningful business for a brand with strong creative identity and growing global recognition.</p>",
        "font_type": "body",
        "vertical_alignment": "start",
        "alignment": "left",
        "color_scheme": "dark_text",
        "margin_top": "none",
        "margin_bot": "none"
      }
    },
    "2_column_text_dcK6L3": {
      "type": "2-column-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_Epn4fK": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "",
            "heading_size": "medium",
            "text": "<p><strong>The Role</strong></p><p>You will lead and grow our UK trade sales across fabric, wallpaper and trim, with a particular focus on interior designers, decorators and boutique retailers.</p><p>This role can be based in:</p><ul><li><strong>East Sussex (near Forest Row)</strong> with regular HQ collaboration</li><li><strong>London</strong>, working remotely with scheduled time in Sussex</li></ul><p>You will be responsible for both strategic direction and hands-on sales execution.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Drive growth within the UK interior design trade sector</li><li>Identify, approach and secure new high-value trade accounts</li><li>Strengthen relationships with existing designers and studios</li><li>Develop a clear trade sales strategy and measurable targets</li><li>Represent Molly Mahon at meetings, studio visits, events and trade shows</li><li>Maintain meticulous follow-up and pipeline management</li><li>Communicate clearly and efficiently with HQ — ensuring all sales details, pricing agreements and client information are organised and recorded</li><li>Work closely with marketing to align trade outreach with campaigns and launches</li></ul><p><strong>Who You Are</strong></p><ul><li>Deeply knowledgeable about the UK interiors trade market</li><li>Well connected with interior designers, decorators and specifiers</li><li>Commercially driven and highly ambitious</li><li>Confident, articulate and persuasive in person and in writing</li><li>Organised and process-driven — you understand that growth requires structure</li><li>Self-motivated and comfortable working remotely</li><li>Energised by craft-led, design-driven brands</li><li>A natural relationship builder with gravitas</li></ul><p>You believe you can materially grow this business — and you can demonstrate how.</p>",
            "button_label": "",
            "button_link": "",
            "inset": false,
            "color_scheme": "dark_text",
            "desktop_text_box_position": "start",
            "text_align": "left"
          }
        },
        "text_QzLTr6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "",
            "heading_size": "medium",
            "text": "<p><strong>What Makes This Different</strong></p><p>This is an opportunity to join a founder-led brand at a pivotal moment. The creative foundation is strong; the commercial opportunity is significant.</p><p>You will have genuine influence over strategy, positioning and growth.</p><p>We are not looking for someone to sit behind a desk. We are looking for someone to step into the industry and confidently say:</p><p>“I believe in what this brand stands for, and I know where it belongs.”</p><p><strong>Package</strong></p><p>Competitive base salary with performance-related commission.<br/>Flexible working structure.<br/>Long-term opportunity to grow with the brand.</p><p>If you are ambitious, well connected and ready to build something meaningful within the interiors industry, we would love to hear from you.</p><p>Please send your CV and a short covering letter outlining how you would approach growing the Molly Mahon trade business.</p><p> </p>",
            "button_label": "",
            "button_link": "",
            "inset": false,
            "color_scheme": "dark_text",
            "desktop_text_box_position": "start",
